4. What is the purpose of ISP? Explain the importance of domain name registration.

Ans. An ISP stands for Internet Service Provider. This is an organization that enables companies and people to connect to the internet and access online services. Different kinds of technologies like wireless networks, cables and satellites etc. to deliver internet connectivity to people. There are several purposes of ISP which are -
a. The primary aim of ISP is providing Internet connections to people. These are generally carried out based on their chosen plans. This is done by broadband services, cable connections etc.

b. ISP assigns IP Address which stands for Internet Protocol to devices that are assigned to different set of devices connected to internet. This helps in efficient communication.

c. ISPs also help users in troubleshooting issues, setting up routers etc for smooth access to internet.

d. Various types of security measures like firewall and parental control features ensures safe browsing.

A domain name is the readable web address that directs users to a specific website. Registration of domain name means officially reserving that address through a recognized registrar. This helps in making it unique to that particular entity. The importance of domain name registration are -
a. A domain name system helps in establishing an online identity.

b. A registered domain establishes trust and enhances credibility that conveys professionalism and trust among online visitors.

c. A domain name caters to a wider audience worldwide therefore increasing viewership.
